    "narrative": "Our offense centers around the elite matchup for **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands the day\u2019s highest projection (83.34) against Ryan Weiss. With a shaky 6.75 xERA opposing him and favorable wind conditions, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is an auto-start with massive ceiling potential. We are also leaning into significant platoon advantages today; **Gleyber Torres** (63.57) benefits from a strong 13% boost against Kyle Harrison, and **Taylor Ward** (63.72) is set to capitalize on favorable park factors and platoon splits against Kris Bubic. Meanwhile, **Daulton Varsho** (67.50) is a high-value play despite the \"Elite Catcher\" defensive penalty; his matchup against Jack Kochanowicz provides enough SP-related upside to outweigh the risks associated with the bottom-third of the batting order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Matt Chapman** (49.36). He was the closest to cracking the starting nine, but the combination of facing a high-caliber arm in Yoshinobu Yamamoto and a 35% rain risk effectively neutralized his output, pushing our optimizer to favor the safer floor provided by **Geraldo Perdomo** (62.94). We are also closely monitoring the lineup status of **Will Smith** and **Luis Arraez**, both of whom carry weather warnings. If the rain risk in their respective games forces a late scratch, we are prepared to pivot to the bench, though we caution that replacing **Luis Arraez** during a start against Yamamoto is a high-variance move given the lack of superior available alternatives today. Proceed with standard caution regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" tags for our catchers, **Will Smith** and **Cal Raleigh**, who remain primary anchors if confirmed in the top-three spots.",
